\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces Self-consistency scaling curves (Phase~1: Haiku, $T = 1.0$, 200 instances). Accuracy vs.\ sample count $N$ for three tasks spanning the bottleneck spectrum. All three curves plateau immediately: maximum lift across 33 samples is 3.0 pp (B4), 1.5 pp (B6), and 1.0 pp (B7). The zero-parameter theoretical prediction using between-model $\rho $ (gray dashed) substantially overestimates improvement for B4 and B7, because $\rho _{\text  {within}} \gg \rho _{\text  {between}}$.}}{9}{figure.caption.16}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:scaling}{{1}{9}{Self-consistency scaling curves (Phase~1: Haiku, $T = 1.0$, 200 instances). Accuracy vs.\ sample count $N$ for three tasks spanning the bottleneck spectrum. All three curves plateau immediately: maximum lift across 33 samples is 3.0 pp (B4), 1.5 pp (B6), and 1.0 pp (B7). The zero-parameter theoretical prediction using between-model $\rho $ (gray dashed) substantially overestimates improvement for B4 and B7, because $\rho _{\text {within}} \gg \rho _{\text {between}}$}{figure.caption.16}{}}
\newlabel{fig:scaling@cref}{{[figure][1][]1}{[1][9][]9}{}{}{}}
